<p>Opportunity cost gets larger when choices are hard to reverse. A regrettable dinner out is recoverable. Ten years of delayed retirement saving is not. Missing the early years of compounding can leave final wealth dramatically lower than most people expect. The same is true outside finance. A burdensome commute, neglected health, or years in the wrong field can consume energy and options in ways that money alone cannot easily repair.</p>
